HABITAT. — We encountered this species under grasses at the edges of ponds and on river banks. It was also found in paddy fields. In the dry season, we collected
P. bibroni
under rocks, deadwood and accumulated dry grass around ponds. The species was found in dry and wet savannah habitats, intermittent freshwater wetlands, rural gardens, heavily degraded forests (agricultural areas), channels and ditches ( Rödel 2000 ). It is a common species, widely distributed in West Africa ( Lamotte & Ohler 1997 ;
Nago et al. 2006
;
Segniagbeto et al. 2007
;
Mohneke et al. 2011
; Onadeko 2016 ;
Sánchez-Vialas et al. 2017
).
